<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="226" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Distribution</emphasis>
. Tropical and subtropical waters in the Pacific, Atlantic, and Indian Oceans. In the eastern Pacific from California to 
<collectingCountry box="[362,413,187,213]" name="Peru" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, M. E. &amp; Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N." box="[428,691,186,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" refId="ref16128" refString="Vinogradov, M. E., Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N. (1996) Hyperiid amphipods (Amphipoda, Hyperiidea) of the world oceans. Oxonian Press Pvt. Ltd., New Delhi, 632 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Vinogradov 
<emphasis box="[569,618,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
, García Madrigal 2007, this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="226" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,222,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Remarks</emphasis>
. Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1847" box="[445,591,222,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oxycephalidae" genus="Rhabdosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[445,591,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Rhabdosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an easily recognized slender and elongated body. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="H. Milne Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Malacostraca" family="Oxycephalidae" genus="Rhabdosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Rhabdosoma armatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished mainly by the shape and proportions of the telson, with double urosomite, and uropods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
Most commonly found in 
<quantity box="[491,589,294,321]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" unit="m" value="37.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="25.0">25‒50 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, M. E. &amp; Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N." box="[672,936,294,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" refId="ref16128" refString="Vinogradov, M. E., Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N. (1996) Hyperiid amphipods (Amphipoda, Hyperiidea) of the world oceans. Oxonian Press Pvt. Ltd., New Delhi, 632 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Vinogradov 
<emphasis box="[813,862,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
). Rare in the southern Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[1275,1389,294,320]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">California</collectingRegion>
and always present in surface waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Siegel-Causey, D." box="[525,755,330,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" refId="ref15575" refString="Siegel-Causey, D. (1982) Factors determining the distribution of hyperiid Amphipoda in the Gulf of California. Ph. D. Thesis, University of Arizona, Tucson, Arizona, 535 pp." type="book" year="1982">Siegel-Causey 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Also recorded in the Mexican portion of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1266,1380,330,356]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">California</collectingRegion>
Current (
<bibRefCitation author="Lavaniegos, B. E. &amp; Hereu, C." box="[209,512,366,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" pagination="137 - 152" refId="ref15092" refString="Lavaniegos, B. E. &amp; Hereu, C. (2009) Seasonal variation in hyperiid amphipod abundance and diversity and influence of mesoscale structures off Baja California. Marine Ecology Progress Series, 394, 137 - 152. https: // doi. org / 10.3354 / meps 08285" type="journal article" year="2009">Lavaniegos &amp; Hereu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Another rare species (
<specimenCount box="[774,942,366,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
in two localities) in our survey (
<figureCitation box="[1306,1375,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1413,1437]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-180@8.[151,1436,489,1390]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Localities where Rhabdosoma armatum, R. brevicaudatum, and R. minor were collected during this survey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6332535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6332535/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
